    • Method Detail

      • open

        boolean open(UniqueSourceInterface source)
        Open a unique instance of an input source. The source "pointer" should be ready to read the first record if successful.
        Returns:
        TRUE if OPEN was successful.

      • nextRecord

        InputRecordInterface nextRecord(UniqueIDInterface source)
        Get the next record from the identified input source. Should return a valid InputRecordInterface, or an InputRecordInvalid object.
        See Also:
        InputRecordInterface, InputRecordInvalid

      • gotoStart

        boolean gotoStart(UniqueIDInterface source)
        Rewind the identified input source to its first record. The source "pointer" should be ready to read the first record on exit.
        Returns:
        TRUE if successful.

      • gotoRecord

        InputRecordInterface gotoRecord(UniqueRecordInterface recordInfo)
        Locate and return the requested record in the input source. The source "pointer" should be ready to read the record AFTER the identified record on exit. Should return a valid InputRecordInterface, or an InputRecordInvalid object.
        See Also:
        InputRecordInterface, InputRecordInvalid

      • close

        void close(UniqueIDInterface source)
        Close the identified input source and release resources.
